HEADWORD: Photomechanical
<hw>Pho`to*me*chan"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, any photographic process in which a
printing surface is obtained without the intervention of hand
engraving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photometer</ent>⟦br⟧
